14/05/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Serbia-Montenegro's Defence Ministry revealed Thursday (13 May) that the federal draft defence strategy has been completed.
Ministry representative Milan Karagac said the final version of the law would be transferred to the federal cabinet, pending adoption, which he expects soon.
The strategy is aimed at enhancing democratic control over the army, in line with NATO standards.
In other news, Federal Defence Minister Prvoslav Davinc said Thursday that the problem of financing the federal army was resolved at Tuesday's session of the Supreme Defence Council.
He did not elaborate.
(B92, Tanjug - 13/05/04)
